<div class="clear"></div></div>			<div class="meta"><a class="g-user-rank-link" href="/user/2096/">yugene</a> at 2010/11/22 01:29pm</div>
			<div class="title">Complex attributes</div>
			<div class="content"><p>Please, notice that here
</p><pre>
<code>'user'=&gt;array(
    'asc'=&gt;'first_name, last_name',
    'desc'=&gt;'first_name DESC, last_name DESC',
    'label'=&gt;'Name'
)
</code></pre>

<p>'user' shouldn't be a valid attribute of the model you're sorting, or you'll get just a simple sort by this attribute.</p>
</div>
					</div>
				<div class="comment alt-1">
			<a class="cid" id="c80" title="permalink to this comment" href="#c80">#80</a>
