<div class="clear"></div></div>			<div class="meta"><a class="g-user-rank-link" href="/user/5310/">CGeorge</a> at 2010/09/21 12:38pm</div>
			<div class="title">Sorting foreign columns</div>
			<div class="content"><p>If you want to sort foreign columns of a related table:</p>

<pre>$sort=new CSort;
$sort-&gt;modelClass='Entity';
$sort-&gt;attributes=array('*');

foreach(Entity::model()-&gt;attributeNames() as $attr)
    $sort-&gt;attributes[]="relatedEntity.$attr";

//Important! The default separator uses a dot for separate the    direction from the attribute, and the related attribute is separated by a dot too!
$sort-&gt;separator=array(',','-');</pre>
</div>
					</div>
			</div>
